        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 4:25PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 425 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Solano, or 13 miles north of Mosquero, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bueyeros.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
